cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with natural language processing and text embeddings. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) because it proposes a learning algorithm for text embeddings. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) because it uses neural networks for learning. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.SD (Sound) because the term "continual multiplication" could be related to sound processing, but this is less likely than the other categories mentioned.
